The crystal structure and degree of crystallinity of the cellulose fibers and CNCs were determined by an X-ray diffraction (XRD) technique, using an X-ray diffractometer (PANalytical, X’Pert PRO) with Cu Kα radiation (λ = 0.15406 nm). The diffractometer was operated at 30 kV, 40 mA, and the sample was scanned over a 2θ range of 5–60°. To determine the crystallinity index (Xc) of the celluloses, the following equation was used:1Xc=[I002-Iam/×100]/I002,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
